## Step 5 — Find the Offending Queries (Historical)

Find which queries have caused the most physical reads since last restart:

```sql
SELECT TOP 20
    qs.total_physical_reads                                     AS total_physical_reads,
    qs.total_physical_reads / qs.execution_count               AS avg_physical_reads,
    qs.total_logical_reads  / qs.execution_count               AS avg_logical_reads,
    qs.total_elapsed_time   / qs.execution_count / 1000        AS avg_duration_ms,
    qs.execution_count,
    t.text                                                      AS query_text,
    qp.query_plan
FROM sys.dm_exec_query_stats qs
CROSS APPLY sys.dm_exec_sql_text(qs.sql_handle) t
CROSS APPLY sys.dm_exec_query_plan(qs.plan_handle) qp
ORDER BY qs.total_physical_reads DESC;
```

> **Tip:** Click the `query_plan` link in SSMS results to open the graphical execution plan. Look for **Table Scan** or **Clustered Index Scan** operators — these are the primary cause of excessive physical reads.

