## Step 8 — Update Statistics

Outdated statistics cause SQL Server to generate poor execution plans, often doing full scans instead of seeks:

```sql
-- Check when stats were last updated
SELECT 
    OBJECT_NAME(s.object_id)    AS table_name,
    s.name                      AS stats_name,
    sp.last_updated,
    sp.rows,
    sp.rows_sampled,
    sp.modification_counter
FROM sys.stats s
CROSS APPLY sys.dm_db_stats_properties(s.object_id, s.stats_id) sp
WHERE OBJECT_NAME(s.object_id) = 'YourTableName'  -- replace with your table
ORDER BY sp.last_updated ASC;

-- Update stats on a specific table with full scan
UPDATE STATISTICS [dbo].[YourTable] WITH FULLSCAN;

-- Update all stats in the database
EXEC sp_updatestats;
```

