## Root Cause Decision Tree

```
IO_COMPLETION waits high?
        │
        ├── avg_io_stall_ms > 30ms?
        │       └── YES → Storage problem
        │               ├── Azure VM? → Upgrade to Premium SSD (Step 9.1)
        │               ├── Backup on same disk? → Separate backup disk
        │               └── Data & Log on same disk? → Separate to different disks (Step 9.3)
        │
        ├── Buffer Cache Hit Ratio < 90%?
        │       └── YES → Not enough RAM
        │               └── Increase max server memory (Step 9.4)
        │
        ├── High physical_reads on specific query?
        │       └── YES → Query problem
        │               ├── Missing index? → Create index (Step 6)
        │               ├── Fragmented index? → Rebuild index (Step 7)
        │               └── Outdated stats? → Update statistics (Step 8)
        │
        └── Backup or DBCC running?
                └── YES → Schedule off-peak hours
```

---

## Common Causes Summary

| Cause | Fix | Step |
|---|---|---|
| Slow HDD / Standard SSD | Upgrade to Premium SSD | Step 9.1 |
| Data & Log on same disk | Separate to different disks | Step 9.3 |
| Not enough RAM / buffer pool | Increase max server memory | Step 9.4 |
| Missing indexes → table scans | Create missing indexes | Step 6 |
| Fragmented indexes | Rebuild / Reorganize indexes | Step 7 |
| Outdated statistics | Run UPDATE STATISTICS | Step 8 |
| Backup running on production disk | Move backup to separate disk | Step 9.3 |
| DBCC CHECKDB during peak hours | Schedule off-peak | — |

